covered:
- streamio: cout, cin
- comments: /**/ or //
- namespace: separation of scope 
- operator orverloading: example "cout <<" whener << is used for directing
  stream to io, where are in  " 0X0F << 4", mean left shift 0xoF by 4 bits.
- function overloading & default values: in C++ we can have same function names
  with different signatures (i.e., arugmnets passed to it). those arguments can
also be assigned default values in case argument is not pass when fucntion is
called.
- REFERENCES: in c++ we use & infront of data type to mark that as reference to
  that variables. (eg: int& a) here we are telling its reference to an integer
variable.
